<section id="about" class="py-24 px-4 sm:px-6 bg-dark-800">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-12 items-center">
    <!-- Author photo placeholder -->
    <div class="flex-shrink-0">
      <div class="w-64 h-64 sm:w-80 sm:h-80 rounded-full bg-dark-600 border-4 border-primary/20 flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden">
        <div class="text-center">
          <svg class="w-20 h-20 text-gray-600 mx-auto mb-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1" d="M16 7a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0zM12 14a7 7 0 00-7 7h14a7 7 0 00-7-7z" />
          </svg>
          <span class="text-gray-500 text-xs">[ Author Photo ]</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Bio -->
    <div class="flex-1 max-w-xl">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
        About Rajko
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Rajko Radivojac is a beekeeper and author with many years of practical experience,
          observation, and education in the field of beekeeping. He has published three
          beekeeping books in Bosnia and Herzegovina and has written more than 40 articles for
          regional beekeeping magazines, establishing a strong and respected presence in
          practical beekeeping literature.
        </p>
        <p>
          His work is shaped by a clear and experience-based style that values practical
          instruction, sound judgment, and a deep understanding of the rhythms of beekeeping
          through the seasons. He writes with the goal of making beekeeping knowledge
          accessible, useful, and grounded in real-world practice.
        </p>
        <p>
          Rajko also served for many years as president of the beekeeping association <strong class="text-white">Prva
          Pčela</strong> in Prijedor, Bosnia and Herzegovina, where he supported the local beekeeping
          community and helped promote the sharing of practical knowledge and experience
          among beekeepers.
        </p>
        <p>
          Since moving to the United States, he has expanded his work into children's literature,
          publishing two picture books under the pen name <strong class="text-white">Ray Smart</strong>. Across both practical
          writing and storytelling, his work reflects a commitment to clear communication,
          meaningful content, and a genuine connection with readers.
        </p>
        <p>
          With a background in book publishing, magazine writing, leadership in the beekeeping
          community, and long-term hands-on practice, Rajko Radivojac brings credibility,
          experience, and dedication to everything he writes.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
